to the editor re the farm bill charade by senator dick lugar op ed jan 21 many price supports for american farmers would not be needed if the federal government followed a sensible and sustainable water policy in the western united states the subsidy of irrigation water to many western farmers allows them to grow unneeded crops on marginal land that otherwise could n't be grown economically if these farmers were charged a realistic price for their water many of these crops would not be grown lessening the need for other farm subsidies across the country daniel lautenbach ann arbor mich jan 21 2002

